# IDStudio.Ai - Windsurf Rules & Session Log

## Project Overview
IDStudio.Ai is a Next.js 14 (App Router) AI-powered platform for interior designers.
- **Stack**: TypeScript, React, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui, Zustand, Framer Motion
- **Backend**: Supabase (PostgreSQL, Auth, Storage)
- **AI**: Anthropic Claude API + Google Gemini
- **Payments**: Stripe subscription management
- **Toast System**: Sonner (already mounted in root layout)
- **Product Clipper**: Chrome extension (`idstudio-clipper` repo) + in-app Product Library at `/dashboard/sourcing`

## Code Conventions
- Use `Anthropic.Tool[]` for tool definitions passed to Claude API (not `as any`)
- Guard debug `console.log` calls behind `process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development'`
- Use `toast.error()` from sonner for user-facing error feedback (Toaster is in `app/layout.tsx`)
- Clean up timers/subscriptions on component unmount via `useRef` + `useEffect` cleanup
- Avoid double-computation in render functions (cache `.split()` results in a variable)
- Webhook handlers must let errors propagate (no try/catch swallowing) so Stripe retries on failure
- Validate all user-supplied redirect URLs against the app's origin before passing to Stripe
- All interactive elements must have `aria-label`; dropdowns need `aria-expanded`, `aria-haspopup`, `role="listbox"`
- Category selectors use `role="tablist"` / `role="tab"` / `aria-selected` pattern
- Chat message containers use `role="log"` with `aria-live="polite"` for screen reader announcements
- Dashboard activity sorting uses raw ISO dates (`createdAt`), not formatted relative strings

