### 2. Guarded debug console.log in chat API route
- **File**: `app/api/chat/route.ts` (line ~199)
- **What**: Wrapped `console.log('[AI Tool]...')` in `process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development'` check
- **Why**: Prevents tool names and inputs from being logged in production server logs

### 3. Replaced `as any` type casts with proper types
- **File**: `app/api/chat/route.ts`
  - `TOOL_DEFINITIONS as any` -> `TOOL_DEFINITIONS as Anthropic.Tool[]`
  - Removed unnecessary `as any` on `completion.content` and `toolResults` in message array construction
- **File**: `app/api/webhooks/route.ts`
  - `(subscription as any).current_period_end` -> `subscription.current_period_end` (property exists on Stripe.Subscription)
  - `(invoice as any).subscription` -> `invoice.subscription` (property exists on Stripe.Invoice)
- **Why**: Improves type safety, enables IDE autocomplete, and catches type errors at compile time

### 4. Added toast notifications for dashboard fetch errors
- **File**: `app/dashboard/page.tsx`
- **What**: Replaced silent `console.error` calls with `toast.error()` from sonner when projects/clients/files fail to load
- **Why**: Users now see visual feedback when data fails to load instead of seeing empty sections with no explanation

### 5. Optimized MessageBubble split logic
- **File**: `components/MessageBubble.tsx`
- **What**: Cached `content.split('\n')` in a `lines` variable instead of calling `.split()` twice per render
- **Why**: Eliminates redundant string splitting on every render cycle

### 6. Fixed setTimeout memory leak on login page
- **File**: `app/login/page.tsx`
- **What**: Stored the redirect `setTimeout` in a `useRef` and added a `useEffect` cleanup to clear it on unmount
- **Why**: Prevents the redirect from firing after the component unmounts if the user navigates away during the 1.2s delay

### 7. Fixed Stripe webhook handlers swallowing errors
- **File**: `app/api/webhooks/route.ts`
- **What**: Removed try/catch blocks from all 5 webhook handler functions (`handleSubscriptionUpdate`, `handleSubscriptionDeleted`, `handlePaymentSucceeded`, `handlePaymentFailed`, `handleTrialWillEnd`). Errors now propagate to the outer handler which returns 500, causing Stripe to retry.
- **Why**: Previously, handlers caught errors and returned normally, so the route always returned 200 OK to Stripe. This made Stripe think the webhook was processed successfully, and it would never retry. Failed subscription updates, payment status changes, and cancellations were silently lost.
- **Also**: Guarded webhook console.logs behind `NODE_ENV === 'development'`

### 8. Added redirect URL validation to checkout and billing portal
- **Files**: `app/api/checkout/route.ts`, `app/api/billing-portal/route.ts`
- **What**: Added origin validation for `successUrl`, `cancelUrl`, and `returnUrl` parameters. Validates that supplied URLs match the app's own origin (derived from `request.url`), preventing open redirect attacks.
- **Why**: Without validation, an attacker could craft a checkout request with a phishing domain as the success URL, tricking users into entering credentials on a lookalike site after payment.

### 9. Added credit fetch error handling in AIChatPanel
- **File**: `components/layout/AIChatPanel.tsx`
- **What**: Replaced empty `catch {}` block with proper error logging and a `toast.error('Unable to load credit balance')` notification for both fetch failures and non-OK responses.
- **Why**: Users previously got no feedback when credit status failed to load. They could attempt messages without knowing their balance, leading to confusing "out of credits" errors mid-conversation.

### 10. Optimized dashboard queries and fixed brittle date sorting
- **File**: `app/dashboard/page.tsx`
- **What**: Reduced query limits from 10 to 5 per table (only 5 items displayed). Added raw `createdAt` field to activity items and replaced the fragile try/catch sort (which was parsing relative strings like "2 hours ago") with a clean `new Date(b.createdAt).getTime()` comparison.
- **Why**: Was fetching 30 rows to show 5. The sort was comparing formatted strings ("2 hours ago") as dates, which silently broke — "2 days ago" and "3 hours ago" both resolved to `Date.now()`, making the sort random.

### 11. Added comprehensive accessibility to AI chat panel
- **File**: `components/layout/AIChatPanel.tsx`
- **What**:
  - Added `aria-label="AI Assistant chat panel"` to the `<aside>` landmark
  - Added `aria-label="Open AI Assistant"` / `"Close AI Assistant"` to toggle buttons
  - Added `aria-expanded`, `aria-haspopup="listbox"`, `aria-label` to model selector button
  - Added `role="listbox"` to model dropdown, `role="option"` + `aria-selected` to each option
  - Added `role="tablist"` to category selector, `role="tab"` + `aria-selected` to each tab
  - Added `role="log"` + `aria-live="polite"` to message container for live announcements
  - Added `aria-label="Message to AI assistant"` to textarea, `aria-label="Send message"` to send button
  - Added keyboard navigation to model dropdown (ArrowUp/Down to cycle, Enter/Space to confirm, Escape to close)
- **Why**: Screen reader users couldn't navigate the chat panel. No interactive elements had labels, the dropdown had no keyboard support, and new messages weren't announced.

